<paragraph blockId="43.[192,1440,259,347]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,735,259,283]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">Identification, taxonomy, and variation.</emphasis>
Adults are bright orange-yellow dorsally and dark basally. Adult wingspan ranges from 
<quantity box="[542,666,291,315]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="43" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="55.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="50.0">50-60 mm</quantity>
. This subspecies somewhat resembles 
<emphasis box="[1129,1277,291,315]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">
S. h. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Edwards" authorityYear="1879" box="[1189,1277,291,315]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argynnis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chitone">chitone</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
but is always silver on the ventral hindwing spots.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[192,897,387,411]" box="[192,897,387,411]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,287,387,411]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">Range.</emphasis>
Kaibab Plateau, near the Grand Canyon, 
<collectingRegion box="[792,892,387,411]" country="United States of America" name="Arizona" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">Arizona</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[192,974,451,475]" box="[192,974,451,475]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,360,451,475]" pageId="43" pageNumber="42">Life history.</emphasis>
